com.buabook.kdb.data

Class KdbTable

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.buabook.kdb.data.KdbTable
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<KdbDict>

    public class KdbTable
extends Object
implements Iterable<KdbDict>

    Table Data Container for kdb

    Data container representing a table that can be serialised and sent to a kdb process (via c)

    Also provides the ability to accept a c.Flip object received from a kdb process and access it within Java, including iterating over it with the KdbDict object.

    Implementation is not thread-safe.

      • fromObject

        public static KdbTable fromObject(Object object)
                           throws ClassCastException

        Generates a new KdbTable object from an object. This method will only succeed if the object provided can be cast into a c.Flip.

        Use this method along with KdbQuery to convert a query result into a table when one is expected.

        Parameters:
        object - The object to generate a new KdbTable from
        Returns:
        A new table or null if the provided object is null
        Throws:
        ClassCastException - If the specified object cannot be cast into a c.Flip
